The paper deals with graph properties and their algorithmic tractability, which suggests that it belongs to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) category. The use of the Poljak-Turzík bound and its generalization for Max-Cut also suggests that it could belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) or Computational Geometry (cs.CG) categories. The mention of FPT algorithms and parameterized complexity suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Finally, the mention of oriented graphs and edge labels suggests that it could belong to the Graph Theory (cs.GT) category.
